HEADWORD: Subordinative
<hw>Sub*or"di*na*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tending to
subordinate; expressing subordination; used to introduce a subordinate
sentence; <as>as, a <ex>subordinative</ex> conjunction</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suborn</ent>⟦br⟧
